<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">A live audio webcast of the presentation will be available in the investors section of our website, <U>www.mondelezinternational.com</U>. An archived replay
of the presentation and the presentation slides will be available on the website for one year following the webcast. The presentation slides, including the related Regulation G reconciliations, are being furnished as Exhibit 99.2 to this Current
Report on Form 8-K. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">This information, including Exhibits 99.1 and 99.2, will not be deemed &#147;filed&#148; for purposes of Section 18 of the Securities
Exchange Act of 1934, as amended (the &#147;Exchange Act&#148;), or otherwise subject to the liabilities under that section, and it will not be incorporated by reference in any filing under the Securities Act of 1933, as amended, or the Exchange
Act, except as expressly set forth by specific reference in such a filing. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="top"><U>ir@mdlz.com</U></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>Mondel&#275;z International Details Long-Term Growth </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>Targets and Margin-Improvement Plans at CAGNY </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">BOCA RATON, Fla. &#150; Feb. 18, 2014 &#150; At the Consumer Analyst Group of New York (CAGNY) conference today, executives of Mondel&#275;z
International highlighted the company&#146;s competitive advantages, long-term growth targets and margin-improvement initiatives. The company also provided detailed insights into the performance and outlook of its North American business. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#147;With an unrivaled portfolio of iconic brands, leading share positions in all of our key categories and an advantaged geographic
footprint, we have the best set of assets in our industry,&#148; said Irene Rosenfeld, Chairman and CEO. &#147;The plans we&#146;re executing now will enable us over the long term to deliver strong top-line growth, significantly expand margins, grow
Adjusted EPS double digits and continue to generate solid cash flow. We believe these efforts will drive top-tier shareholder returns.&#148; </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Snacking:
A $1.2 Trillion Opportunity with Attractive Growth Prospects </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The company highlighted that snacking is a $1.2 trillion market
worldwide, offering attractive growth and margin prospects. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#147;Historically, our snacks categories have grown at rates of around 6
percent,&#148; Rosenfeld said. &#147;Although categories have slowed recently, we expect snacks categories will recover, as they are well-aligned with consumer needs to fuel our bodies, treat ourselves and boost our minds. In fact, consumers
continue to move away from large meals at fixed times to more frequent and smaller snacking occasions. Snacks consumption also increases as GDP per capita rises in emerging markets like Brazil, Russia, India and China.&#148; </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In addition, snacks carry higher margins than many other food products due to low private label penetration and a large percentage of sales
from immediate consumption channels. </P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Supply Chain Reinvention and &#145;Fit For Purpose&#146; Overheads to Expand Margins </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Dave Brearton, Executive Vice President and CFO, highlighted the company&#146;s initiatives to expand margins, including improvements to
Adjusted Operating Income margin of 500 and 250 basis points in North America and Europe, respectively, by 2016. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The biggest driver
behind these targets is the reinvention of the supply chain. Over the next three years, the company expects to deliver $3 billion in gross productivity savings, $1.5 billion in net productivity and $1 billion in incremental cash. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Brearton highlighted that significant progress has already been made. To date, 30 plants have been streamlined, closed or sold. At the same
time, the company is building leading-edge facilities in Mexico and India and significantly expanding facilities in the Czech Republic, the UK and the U.S. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#147;Overhead savings will also be a major contributor to margin gains,&#148; said Brearton. &#147;We&#146;re accelerating our cost-reduction
efforts by ensuring that our overheads are &#145;fit for purpose&#146; for the size and scope of our company and by adopting zero-based budgeting.&#148; </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Putting it all together, the company affirmed the following long-term targets: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="9%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Organic Net Revenue growth: At or above category growth </TD></TR></TABLE>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="9%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Adjusted Operating Income growth: High single-digit growth at constant currency </TD></TR></TABLE>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="9%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Adjusted EPS growth: Double-digit growth at constant currency </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Sustaining Growth and Expanding Margin in
North America </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Mark Clouse, EVP and President, North America, detailed the company&#146;s strategic plans to deliver sustainable
revenue growth and improve margins in its $7 billion business in the U.S. and Canada. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#147;By focusing on our Power Brands, innovation
platforms and our Direct Store Delivery operation, we expect to deliver sustainable growth and outpace our competitors. And through better cost management and the reinvention of our supply chain, we&#146;ll significantly expand our margins to bring
us in line with our peers,&#148; said Clouse. &#147;In 2013, we delivered strong growth on the top line and made significant progress against our 500-point margin expansion target.&#148; </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">A live audio webcast of the CAGNY presentation will be available in the investors section of the company&#146;s website
(<U>www.mondelezinternational.com</U>) at 12:30 p.m. ET today. An archived replay of the presentation with accompanying slides will be available on the website for one year following the webcast. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">2 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>About Mondel&#275;z International </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Mondel&#275;z International, Inc. (NASDAQ: MDLZ) is a global snacking powerhouse, with 2013 revenue of $35 billion. Creating delicious moments
of joy in 165 countries, Mondel&#275;z International is a world leader in chocolate, biscuits, gum, candy, coffee and powdered beverages, with billion-dollar brands such as <I>Cadbury</I>,<I> Cadbury Dairy Milk</I> and <I>Milka</I> chocolate,
<I>Jacobs</I> coffee, <I>Oreo, LU</I> and <I>Nabisco</I> biscuits, <I>Tang</I> powdered beverages and <I>Trident</I> gum. Mondel&#275;z International is a proud member of the Standard and Poor&#146;s 500, NASDAQ 100 and Dow Jones Sustainability
Index. Visit <U>www.mondelezinternational.com</U> and <U>www.facebook.com/mondelezinternational</U>. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Forward-Looking Statements </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">This press release contains a number of forward-looking statements. Words, and variations of words, such as &#147;will,&#148;
&#147;expect,&#148; &#147;believe,&#148; &#147;deliver&#148; and similar expressions are intended to identify our forward-looking statements. Examples of forward-looking statements include, but are not limited to, statements we make about our future
performance, including future revenue growth, earnings per share, operating income, margins, cash flow and shareholder returns; and the drivers of our future performance, including investments, productivity improvements and cost reductions. These
forward-looking statements are subject to a number of risks and uncertainties, many of which are beyond our control, which could cause our actual results to differ materially from those indicated in our forward-looking statements. Such factors
include, but are not limited to, risks from operating globally and in emerging markets, continued consumer weakness, continued volatility of commodity and other input costs, pricing actions, continued weakness in economic conditions, business
disruptions, increased competition and tax law changes. For additional information on these and other factors that could affect our forward-looking statements, see our risk factors, as they may be amended from time to time, set forth in our filings
with the SEC, including our most recently filed Annual Report on Form 10-K. We disclaim and do not undertake any obligation to update or revise any forward-looking statement in this press release, except as required by applicable law or regulation.
</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">

<div style='position:absolute;left:107px;top:452px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:8px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>Indemnification Agreement dated May 1, 2008 (&#147;Tax Indemnity&#148;) for certain
2007 and 2008 transactions relating to the demerger of Cadbury&#146;s Americas Beverage business.&nbsp; A U.S. federal tax audit of </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:107px;top:462px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:8px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>DPSG for the 2006&#45;2008 tax years was concluded with the IRS in August 2013. As
a result, the company recorded a favorable impact of $363 million due to the reversal of the accrued liability in </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:107px;top:472px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:8px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>excess of the amount paid to DPSG under the Tax Indemnity. The company recorded
$336 million in selling, general and administrative expenses and $49 million in interest and other expense, net,</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:107px;top:481px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:8px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>partially offset by $22 million of tax expense for an impact of $0.20 per diluted
share.</div> <div style='position:absolute;left:107px;top:492px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:8px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>On February 22, 2013, the company acquired the remaining interest in a
biscuit operation in Morocco, which is now a wholly&#45;owned subsidiary within the EEMEA segment.&nbsp; A pre&#45;tax gain of $22 </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:107px;top:502px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:8px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>million was recorded in connection with the acquisition.&nbsp; In addition, during
the twelve months ended December 31, 2013, the company divested a salty snack business in Turkey, a confectionery </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:107px;top:512px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:8px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>business in South Africa and a chocolate business in Spain.&nbsp; A pre&#45;tax
gain of $8 million was recorded in connection with these divestitures.</div>
